# Template Initialization Guide

Step-by-step guide to bootstrap a new project from this template.

## Prerequisites

- Node.js 20+
- pnpm (`npm install -g pnpm`)
- Expo CLI (`npm install -g expo-cli`)
- EAS CLI (`npm install -g eas-cli`)
- An Expo account with a project created at https://expo.dev

## 1. Update Project Identity

### `package.json`

Change these fields:

```json
{
  "name": "<new-project-name>",
  "version": "1.0.0"
}
```

### `app.json`

```json
{
  "expo": {
    "name": "<new-project-name>",
    "slug": "<new-project-name>",
    "scheme": "<new-project-name>",
    "owner": "<expo-username>",
    "version": "1.0.0"
  }
}
```

### `app.config.ts`

Update the fallback defaults (used when env vars are not set):

```typescript
const expoProjectId = process.env.EXPO_PROJECT_ID ?? '<your-expo-project-id>';
// ...
slug: process.env.EXPO_SLUG ?? '<new-project-name>',
name: process.env.EXPO_NAME ?? '<New Project Name>',
// ...
bundleIdentifier: process.env.EXPO_IOS_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER ?? 'com.<org>.<new-project-name>',
// ...
package: process.env.EXPO_ANDROID_PACKAGE ?? 'com.<org>.<new-project-name>',
```

> Get your Expo project ID from https://expo.dev > Your Project > Settings > Project ID

## 2. Environment Configuration

### `.env.dev.example`

```
ENV=development
API_URL=https://example.com
EXPO_SLUG=<new-project-name>-dev
EXPO_NAME="DEV - <New Project Name>"
EXPO_PROJECT_ID=<your-expo-project-id>
EXPO_IOS_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER=com.<org>.<new-project-name>.dev
EXPO_ANDROID_PACKAGE=com.<org>.<new-project-name>.dev
```

### `.env.prod.example`

```
ENV=production
API_URL=https://example.com
EXPO_SLUG=<new-project-name>
EXPO_NAME="<New Project Name>"
EXPO_PROJECT_ID=<your-expo-project-id>
EXPO_IOS_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER=com.<org>.<new-project-name>
EXPO_ANDROID_PACKAGE=com.<org>.<new-project-name>
```

### `.env.dev`

Copy the dev example to create your local env file:

```bash
cp .env.dev.example .env.dev
```

> `.env.dev` is gitignored. Each developer creates their own copy locally.

## 3. Theme Colors (Optional)

Edit `theme/colors.ts` to change the color palette:

```typescript
export const colors = {
  darkBlue: '#0A1929',      // Headers, dark backgrounds
  blue: '#0066FF',           // Primary buttons, accents
  lightBlue: '#3399FF',      // Active tab, links
  lightGrayBlue: '#F0F4F8',  // Light mode backgrounds
  accentBlue: '#00BFFF',     // Secondary accents
  gray: '#797777',           // Muted text
  blackGray: '#101212',      // Dark mode backgrounds
  black: '#000000',
  white: '#ffffff',
  transparent: 'transparent',
};
```

Files that reference colors (update if you rename properties):
- `app/+not-found.tsx`
- `app/(main)/(tabs)/_layout.tsx`
- `app/(main)/(tabs)/home/_layout.tsx`
- `app/(main)/(tabs)/profile/_layout.tsx`
- `scenes/home/Home.tsx`
- `scenes/profile/Profile.tsx`
- `scenes/details/Details.tsx`
- `components/layouts/BottomSheetContents/BottomSheetContents.tsx`

## 4. Update Branding Text

| File | What to change |
|---|---|
| `components/layouts/BottomSheetContents/BottomSheetContents.tsx` | "Welcome to Glamour" title |
| `components/layouts/DrawerContents/DrawerContents.tsx` | "Glamour" text |
| `README.md` | Project description |
| `LICENSE` | Copyright holder |

## 5. App Icons & Splash Screen

Replace these image files with your own:
- `assets/images/logo-lg.png` - App icon and splash screen image
- `assets/images/logo-sm.png` - Android adaptive icon and web favicon

Splash screen colors are configured in both `app.json` and `app.config.ts`.

## 6. Install & Verify

```bash
# Install dependencies
pnpm install

# Initialize git
git init

# Set up Husky pre-commit hooks
pnpm run prepare

# Verify everything works
pnpm run lint          # Should have 0 errors
pnpm run test          # Should pass all tests
pnpm run dev:web       # Should launch in browser
```

## 7. Initial Commit

```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Initial project setup"
```

## Quick Reference: Project Structure

```
app/                 # Expo Router routes (keep minimal, delegate to scenes)
components/
  elements/          # Reusable UI components (Button, Image, etc.)
  layouts/           # Layout components (headers, drawers, bottom sheets)
scenes/              # Screen components (main UI logic)
hooks/               # Custom React hooks
slices/              # Redux Toolkit slices
services/            # API and external services
theme/               # Colors, fonts, styling system
types/               # TypeScript type definitions
utils/               # Utility functions (config, deviceInfo)
providers/           # React context providers (Redux store)
assets/              # Fonts, images
```

## Quick Reference: Key Config Files

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `.npmrc` | pnpm config (`node-linker=hoisted` required for Expo) |
| `.env.dev` | Local development environment variables |
| `app.json` | Expo static config (name, slug, icons, splash) |
| `app.config.ts` | Expo dynamic config (reads env vars, sets bundle IDs) |
| `utils/config.ts` | Runtime access to env vars via `expo-constants` |
| `eslint.config.mjs` | ESLint 9 flat config |
| `tsconfig.json` | TypeScript strict mode config |
| `jest.config.ts` | Jest test runner config |
